data.enText: to cut up a dead person, animal or plant in order to study it

data.chText: 仔细研究；详细评论；剖析
data.enText: to study sth closely and/or discuss it in great detail

data.chText: 评论家对她最近出版的一部小说作了详细剖析。
data.enText: Her latest novel was dissected by the critics.
to divide sth into smaller pieces, areas, etc.

data.chText: 古老的运河网将这座城市分割开来。
data.enText: The city is dissected by a network of old canals.

data.chText: 对一部小说过多的剖析可能会影响你对它的欣赏。
data.enText: Your enjoyment of a novel can suffer from too much analysis and dissection.

simple_means.memory_skill: dis 加强 + sect 切，割 → 切分 → 解剖

tr: make a mathematical, chemical, or grammatical analysis of
break down into components or essential features

value.def: If someone dissects the body of a dead person or animal, they carefully cut it up in order to examine it scientifically.

example.ex: We dissected a frog in biology class.
example.tran: 我们在生物课上解剖了一只青蛙。

example.ex: Researchers need a growing supply of corpses for dissection.
example.tran: 研究人员需要更多的供解剖用的尸体。

value.def: If someone dissects something such as a theory, a situation, or a piece of writing, they consider and talk about each detail of it.

example.ex: People want to dissect his work and question his motives.
example.tran: 人们想仔细分析他的作品，并对他的动机提出质疑。

example.ex: ...her calm, condescending dissection of my proposals.
example.tran: 她对我的提议居高临下的冷静剖析

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to cut, to divide 切, 割
rootsaffixes.title: sect, seg

partsOfSpeech.dec: bi 二 + sect 切，割 → 二等分
dis 加强 + sect 切，割 → 切分 → 解剖
dissect 解剖 + ion 表名词 → 解剖
inter 在…之间 + sect 切，割 → 从中间切开 → 横切
intersect 横切；交叉 + ion 表名词 → 横切；交叉
sect 切，割 + ion 表名词 → 切开；部门
section 切开；部门 + al …的 → 可组合的；部门的
sect 切，割 + or 表名词 → 部分；部门
seg 切，割 + ment 具体物 → 切开后的东西 → 切片
segment 部分；切片 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 割成几部分 → 分裂
tran〔= trans 横〕+ sect 切，割 → 横着切 → 横断
vivi 活 + sect 切，割 → 活着切开 → 活体解剖
